The paper deals with the problem of sum rate maximization in a bidirectional relay network with fading, which involves the optimization of transmission mode selection and power allocation based on instantaneous channel state information. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). However, given the focus on wireless communication and optimization of transmission modes and power allocation, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.CE.
